quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  10,89,"He said, “Your<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>prayer has been responded to, so be upright and do not follow the way of those who do not know.”"
  10,90,"And We made the Children of Israel pass over the sea. So Pharaoh and his troops pursued them oppressively and aggressively until, when he was about to drown, he said, “I have attained <span class=""h"">belief that<sup foot_note=""80235"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>there is no god except the One the Children of Israel believe in, and I am of the Muslims<a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>.”"
  10,91,"Now? While before you truly disobeyed and were of the corrupters?"
  10,92,"Rather, today We <span class=""h"">deliver<sup foot_note=""80236"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>you, preserving only your body, so that you become a sign for those after you. But most surely, many among mankind are oblivious of Our signs."
  10,93,"And We settled the Children of Israel in an agreeable location and provided them with good things, so they did not differ until knowledge came to them. Indeed, your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord{1}judges between them on the Day of Resurrection regarding whatever they used to differ over.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 1st person to 3rd person.
  10,94,"So if you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>are in doubt about what We have sent down to you, then ask those who recite the Scripture before you. Very truly, the truth has come to you from your Lord<a class=""sup""><sup>e </sup></a>, so never be of the skeptics,"
  10,95,"and never be of those who have disbelieved in Allah’s signs lest you become of the losers."
  10,96,"Indeed, those against whom your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord’s <span class=""h"">Word<sup foot_note=""80238"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span> proved true do not believe,"
  10,97,"even if every sign comes to them—until they see the painful punishment."
